Package de.fraunhofer.iais.eis

Interface LogicalConstraint

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AbstractConstraint, ModelClass
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LogicalConstraintImpl
    public interface LogicalConstraint
extends AbstractConstraint
    The class of Logical Constraints that restrict a Rule. A Logical Constraints is a collection of Constraints, related with each other through the ids:operand property.

        java.util.List<Constraint> getAnd()
        The 'and' operand connects a rdf:List of Constraints with the Boolean operator 'AND'. All Constraints of an 'and' relation must be satisfied at the same time. Only one of ids:and, ids:or, or ids:xone can be used for a specific ids:LogicalConstraint! More information under https://w3id.org/idsa/core/and
